## 2. Test Structure

**Layout policy: `src/`-co-located** — tests live next to the source they exercise (toolkit default).

Each `src/<module>.ts` has a sibling `src/<module>.test.ts` next to it. No separate `tests/` mirror. This matches the gate's existing permissive behavior, removes the placeholder workaround needed for the mirror layout, and follows mainstream Bun/TS convention.

```
src/
├── foo.ts
├── foo.test.ts        # co-located unit test
├── bar.ts
├── bar.test.ts
└── e2e/
    ├── checkout.ts
    └── checkout.test.ts
```

Override to `tests/-mirror` only if your project has a strong reason — declare it in CLAUDE.md `## Testing Conventions` § Layout (e.g., `- **Layout:** tests/-mirror`); `/gate-check` probe #20 reads the declaration and enforces it.

## 3. Conventions

### Naming
- Files: `*.test.ts` / `*_test.dart` / `test_*.py`
- Names: Describe expected behavior

### What to Test
- Happy path, error cases, edge cases, integration points
<!-- ADAPT: Examples — API contract tests, snapshot tests for components (TypeScript); golden tests for widgets, BLoC state transition tests (Flutter); parametrized tests for edge cases, fixture-based integration tests (Python) -->

### What NOT to Test
- Implementation details, third-party internals, generated code

